[medium] src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue:1038 (concurrency/races)
The new optional dashboard-suggestions config/state load is awaited before the core controls page loads profile bindings and control implementations. While that config request is in flight, profileBindingsLoading remains false and activeProfile is still null, so the page can sit on the misleading linked-profile error state and delay all normal controls data behind an AI-only feature request; a slow or hanging /api/dashboard-suggestions/config now blocks the base Controls view.
Suggested fix: Start the AI config/dashboard-suggestion load independently of the main controls initialization, or run it in parallel with loadProfileBindings/loadControlImplementations. For example, fire an async task for fetchDashboardSuggestionsConfig()+loadDashboardSuggestionState(), and keep the existing profile/catalog/control implementation load sequence on the primary onMounted path.
Guidance: In src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue, change onMounted so dashboard-suggestions initialization is not awaited before the core Controls page loads. The AI config and drawer suggestion state are optional; profile bindings, catalog loading, and control implementations must start immediately. Add a small non-blocking helper near loadDashboardSuggestionState, for example async function initializeDashboardSuggestionState() { try { await aiConfigStore.fetchDashboardSuggestionsConfig(); if (aiConfigStore.dashboardSuggestionsEnabled) await loadDashboardSuggestionState(); } catch { /* store/useDataApi already owns AI config error state; do not block controls */ } }. In onMounted, call void initializeDashboardSuggestionState(); before or alongside the existing profile/control load code, but do not await it on the main path. Keep the existing loadProfileBindings sequence and loadControlImplementations try/catch unchanged except for removing the AI awaits ahead of them. Be careful not to remove the config/SSP watcher: it still needs to react when the config flips to enabled or SSP changes. If the previous duplicate-fetch in-flight guard exists, leave it in place; otherwise either rely on the watcher as the single owner of loadDashboardSuggestionState after config fetch, or add the in-flight guard so the helper and watcher cannot double-request. Add/update an IndexView test using a deferred fetchDashboardSuggestionsConfig promise: mount the view, do not resolve the config promise, flush promises, and assert loadProfileBindings/loadControlImplementations side effects occur (or the controls render/loading state advances) before the AI config request resolves.
